&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you an experienced communications professional looking for a new challenge in a developing team? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Lancashire and South Cumbria NHS Foundation Trust is delivering an ambitious and extensive improvement programme which has some exciting but challenging objectives for the communications team. We need someone who can come in and get stuck in straight away. It’s a great time to be joining us – we’re re-designing channels, establishing a new brand, developing critical internal communications and are open to new ideas across our portfolio about how we could do things better, so this is a chance to really shape the future direction of our communications. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for dynamic candidates who bring enthusiasm and a ‘can do’ approach, can motivate a team and deliver high standards at a relentless pace. If that sounds like you – please get in touch for an informal conversation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sam Thomas by emailing sam.thomas@lscft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
